name: Brighton vs Chelsea
summary: Chelsea's push for European qualification received a boost with a 2-1 victory away at Brighton. The Blues took an early lead through Cole Palmer before Leandro Trossard equalized for the hosts. After Reece James was sent off for a handball in the penalty area, Christopher Nkunku netted a second-half winner. The match was broadcast live on BT Sport 1, with highlights available on platforms like Football.London and Eurosport. Brighton's starting lineup included Steele, Lamptey, Veltman, Dunk, Colwill, Sarmiento, Caicedo, March, Gross, Welbeck, and Trossard, while Chelsea fielded Kepa, James, Chalobah, Koulibaly, Cucurella, Gallagher, Kovacic, Mount, Ziyech, Palmer, and Sterling. The victory moves Chelsea into sixth place in the Premier League standings, while Brighton remains in eighth.

name: Andy Murray
summary: Andy Murray is set to make his comeback from injury in Bordeaux, before returning to defend his Surbiton Trophy title as part of his preparation for Wimbledon. The former world No. 1 has made a major change to his game, ditching the brand he has used for 20 years and switching to Yonex rackets. Despite being in the latter stages of his career, Murray is still searching for something extra and has made an interesting change ahead of the French Open. He recently gave a hilarious take on Finland's entry for Eurovision 2024, showcasing his humor alongside his sporting achievements.

name: Alice Munro
summary: Alice Munro, the renowned Nobel Prize-winning short story writer, passed away at 92. Her legacy as a literary giant is evident in the tributes paid by the Guardian, Independent, BBC, and TIME, praising her for reinvigorating the short story genre and exemplifying the "writer's writer." The New York Times and Washington Post highlight the profound impact of her stories, while Literary Hub and the Bookseller celebrate her lasting contributions. The New Statesman acknowledges her as a master of her craft, whose absence will be deeply felt in the literary world.

name: Prairie
summary: The beloved "Little House on the Prairie" is making headlines once again. The iconic farmhouse from the beloved television series "Fixer Upper" is now available for sale (Yahoo Movies UK). Meanwhile, the original cast reunited in Pepin for the show's 50th anniversary (WEAU). Ken Lassman shares his column on the prairie in The Lawrence Times. In other news, Utah authorities discuss efforts to protect endangered prairie dogs (Utah Division of Wildlife Resources), while a mobility scooter driver has tragically died in a vehicle incident in Sun Prairie (WMTV). Prairie Fare highlights the nutritional benefits of gardening (Farm Forum). The Philosophy of Being Offended and "The Fall Guy" are also featured in Prairie Public Broadcasting. Lastly, an evacuation order is in place for residents of Grande Prairie County due to a wildfire in the area (Edmonton Journal and The Alberta Wildfire Blog).
